results.purpose: Track and manage trial box subscription resets for TPT (pet food) customers in KN (Kenya) market who experienced payment failures, and cancel subscriptions after 5+ failed attempts

entities.name: TPT (The Pet Table)
entities.context: Pet food subscription service offering trial boxes to new customers

entities.name: New Ventures Tech team
entities.context: Engineering team responsible for manually resetting subscriptions back to trial SKU

entities.name: BOB (Back Office Backend)
entities.context: Tool used for bulk subscription cancellations and management

entities.name: Databricks
entities.context: Database platform where queries are executed to identify affected subscriptions

entities.name: #squad-nv-pet-food
entities.context: Slack channel for coordinating with engineers on subscription reset tasks

insights: Two-tier process: subscriptions with 5+ failed payments are canceled immediately, while those with fewer failures are reset to trial status
Bi-weekly schedule: queries run on Tuesdays (covering Sat-Tue deliveries) and Fridays (covering Wed-Fri deliveries)
Trial boxes are smaller and lower-priced than regular boxes, requiring special handling to honor promotional pricing
Process prevents indefinite order creation for failed payments by implementing a 4-week reset limit
Only affects non-shipped trial boxes with payment errors (dunning_decision = 'cancel') for new customers (loyalty = 0)
Manual engineering intervention required via Slack ticket system for subscription resets
Workflow includes data validation, bulk cancellation via CSV upload, and cross-team coordination
